OL,3,CNine grieving families call for public
OL,4,Cinquiry into Sussex maternity services
OL,6,FNine families who lost babies at
OL,7,Fhospitals run by the University
OL,8,FHospitals Sussex NHS Foundation Trust
OL,9,Fsay they want a public inquiry into
OL,10,Fthe standard of its maternity care.
OL,12,FTogether, they've sent a letter to
OL,13,Fpoliticians asking for action after
OL,14,Fthe babies died between 2021 and 2023.
OL,16,FAll, they say, died due to preventable
OL,17,Fmistakes in care.
OL,19,FChloe Vowells-Lovett's daughter Esme
OL,20,Fdied at birth, her heart not beating.
